        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 23 at 5:14PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 514 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 15
miles west of Kenton, or 33 miles north of Clayton, moving east at 30
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southwestern Baca
and southeastern Las Animas Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
